records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 3, disorderly conduct.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 2, resist officer and criminal trespass.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Undergo a psychological evaluation and follow through with all recommendations;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety except for lawfully prescribed medications which are taken in prescribed doses;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
6) pay $30.00 restitution to Holley Melichar;
7) Spend four (4) days in the county jail, Ordinary confinement, commencing immediately;
8) Spend  an additional forty-one (41) days in the county jail, Ordinary confinement, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
9) Pay court costs;
10) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
11) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge.  (if it is determined that the defendant has already submitted to a sample, then the surcharges will not be imposed)
(Per Sgt. Brixius at MTSO, the defendants DNA is already on file.  No sample needed to be submitted and therefore no surcharges will be imposed)
Minutes.
